cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.SD, cs.CL 

This paper combines technology use logs with surveys on moral views, human values, and emotional contagion to model physical exercise behavior. The study focuses on the adoption of Health & Fitness mobile applications and proposes design guidelines for persuasive technologies targeting health behavior modification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the intersection of technology and society. The paper also involves machine learning techniques to predict exercise behavior, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the study involves human-computer interaction and user behavior, which could be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also analyzes the relationship between exercise behavior and socioeconomic status, which could be classified under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques to analyze survey responses, which could be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
